          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἁνδάνω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝανδάνω</span>, (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ς</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝηδύς</span>), ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑήνδανε,
            ἥνδανε</span>, perf. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑᾱδότα</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὔαδε</span>
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔϝαδε</span>) and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἅδε</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be acceptable, please</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span>, often w. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θῡμῷ</span> added; impers., or with a thing as subj., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δίχα δέ σφισιν ἥνδανε βουλή,</span>
